01.
select different cities from station table.
and these cities should not end with vowels.
duplicate cities can not be retrieved.

| Field  | Type |
| ------ | ------------- |
| ID     | NUMBER        |
| CITY   | VARCHAR2(21)  |
| STATE  | VARCHAR2(21)  |
| LAT_N  | NUMBER        |
| LONG_W | NUMBER        |


SELECT DISTINCT CITY
FROM STATION
WHERE RIGHT(CITY,1) NOT IN ('A','E','I','O','U')

-- RIGHT FUNCTION used to get cities that are relevant for this question
first mention attribute name which is CITY.
second mention what character is we want to from end. 1 is the last character. 

02.
Query a list of CITY names from STATION for cities that have an even ID number. Print the results in any order, but exclude duplicates from the answer.
The STATION table is described as follows:

| Field  | Type |
| ------ | ------------- |
| ID     | NUMBER        |
| CITY   | VARCHAR2(21)  |
| STATE  | VARCHAR2(21)  |
| LAT_N  | NUMBER        |
| LONG_W | NUMBER        |

SELECT DISTINCT CITY 
FROM STATION 
WHERE MOD(ID,2)=0 
ORDER BY CITY ASC;  

SELECT DISTINCT CITY
FROM STATION
WHERE ID % 2 = 0
ORDER BY CITY ASC;


03. Query the list of CITY names ending with vowels (a, e, i, o, u) from STATION. Your result cannot contain duplicates
SELECT DISTINCT(CITY) 
FROM STATION 
WHERE CITY LIKE '%a' OR CITY LIKE '%e' OR CITY LIKE '%i' OR CITY LIKE '%o' OR CITY LIKE '%u';     


